The paper deals with cache allocation strategies for processing big data workloads in a multi-tenant setting, which involves distributed computing and database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of massively parallel databases, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The fairness model and algorithms developed in the paper involve game theory concepts, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of randomization and algorithms, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
